<doc id="251642" wikidata="Q2963784" url="?curid=251642" title="Chiniquodontidae">
<text>Chiniquodontidae is an extinct family of basal probainognathian cynodonts that lived in what is now Africa and South America during the Middle and Late Triassic. It is currently thought to include four valid genera: &quot;Aleodon&quot;, &quot;Chiniquodon&quot;, &quot;Cromptodon&quot; and &quot;Riojanodon&quot;. Two additional genera (&quot;Belesodon&quot; and &quot;Probelesodon&quot;) are usually regarded as junior synonyms of &quot;Chiniquodon&quot;.

== References ==</text><links>
